      intro:
        "These are the questions our editors hear most often about MEPCO. Every answer cites a primary source where applicable â€” NEPRA tariff orders, PITC consumer master, MEPCO official site, and the Electricity Act 1910 as amended.",
      sections: [],
      faq: [
        { q: "What is the MEPCO reference number?", a: "A 14-digit identifier printed at the top-right of every bill. The only number you need to view, download, or pay your bill online." },
        { q: "How do I check my MEPCO bill online?", a: "Enter the 14-digit reference into the form at the top of this page. We fetch the bill in real time from PITC and display it in a sandboxed iframe. No login, no fee." },
        { q: "Is there an official MEPCO app?", a: "Yes â€” \"MEPCO Multan Electric Power Company\" on Google Play. No official iOS app yet; iPhone users should bookmark this page or bill.pitc.com.pk/mepcobill." },
        { q: "What is the MEPCO customer-care number?", a: "Universal DISCO helpline 118 (toll-free, 24x7). For escalations: gm.cs@mepco.com.pk." },
        { q: "Why is my MEPCO bill higher than last month?", a: "Slab transition (crossing 200 or 700 units), FPA spike (Fuel Price Adjustment notified by NEPRA monthly), or meter-reader error. See the hub page for the full diagnostic." },
        { q: "How long does payment take to reflect?", a: "JazzCash, Easypaisa, NayaPay, SadaPay, and bank-app payments via 1Link: instant. Cash at MEPCO counters or authorised bank branches: 4 working hours. Cheques: 2-3 working days." },
        { q: "What if my MEPCO bill is wrong?", a: "Visit your local SDO with the bill. The SDO can correct meter-reader errors and issue a fresh bill within 7 working days. Escalate to GM CS after 15 days." },
        { q: "How do I switch to the protected tariff?", a: "Register on the Cross Subsidy Program at css.pitc.com.pk. Eligibility requires a six-month rolling average at or below 200 units/month and one live connection per CNIC. See our CSS guide." },
        { q: "Can I pay my MEPCO bill from outside Pakistan?", a: "Yes â€” through your Pakistani bank's mobile app. JazzCash and Easypaisa require a Pakistani SIM for OTP." },
        { q: "What is the MEPCO late-payment penalty?", a: "10% of the energy-charge portion if paid between due date and disconnection date. After disconnection, a reconnection fee of Rs 200-1,000 is added." },
        { q: "How do I apply for a new MEPCO connection?", a: "Online via mepco.com.pk â†’ New Connection or at any subdivision office. See the new-connection spoke for the full document checklist and timeline." },
        { q: "Why is my consumer name wrong on the bill?", a: "Apply for Change of Name (CON) at your local subdivision. Documents: sale deed, both CNICs, last paid bill (no arrears), Rs 200 fee. Takes 15 working days." },
        { q: "Is MEPCO available outside southern Punjab?", a: "No. MEPCO covers only 13 districts of southern Punjab. Other DISCOs cover the rest of Pakistan: LESCO (Lahore/Kasur/Okara/Sheikhupura), IESCO (Islamabad/Rawalpindi), FESCO (Faisalabad), GEPCO (Gujranwala/Sialkot), PESCO (Peshawar), HESCO (Hyderabad), SEPCO (Sukkur), QESCO (Quetta/Balochistan), TESCO (tribal districts), HAZECO (Hazara), and K-Electric (Karachi)." },
        { q: "Does MEPCO offer net-metering?", a: "Yes. Residential systems up to 25 kW. AEDB-registered installer required. Timeline 60-90 days end-to-end." },
        { q: "Are MEPCO bills accepted as proof of address?", a: "Yes. The PDF downloaded from this page carries the PITC verification stamp and is accepted by all Pakistani banks, NADRA, the passport office, and consular departments â€” provided the bill is dated within the last 3 months and the name on the bill matches the applicant." },
      ],
